ISSUE TITLE: Selecting a custom agent at session creation is ignored — session starts with the default agent
ISSUE BODY: When creating a new session in the Agents window and selecting a custom agent (e.g. **Agents Window Developer**) for a Copilot session from Agent Host, the created session does **not** use the selected custom agent — it starts with the **default** agent instead.

## Steps
1. Open the Agents window → New Sessions view.
2. Select the **vscode** folder using a Copilot session from Agent Host (this is needed to see the **Agents Window Developer** custom agent), and a worktree.
3. Select the **Agents Window Developer** custom agent.
4. Create/start the session.

🐛 The session runs the **default** agent, not the selected custom agent.


